oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Johnny Cash live at Annex 14 NCO Club - Long Binh, Vietnam - 1969-01
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Live performances at Annex 14 NCO Club in Long Binh, Vietnam, featuring Johnny Cash (performer), Carl Perkins (performer), and June Carter Cash (performer) from January, 1969.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:creator: Carl Perkins; Johnny Cash; June Carter
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dcterms:tableOfContents: I Walk The Line (band) -- [Unidentified] talks and introduces Carl Perkins -- Free Born Man (Carl Perkins) -- Carl Perkins talks and thanks the soldiers for their service -- Mean Woman Blues (Carl Perkins) -- Carl Perkins introduces the next tune -- I Can't Help It (If I'm Still In Love With You) (Carl Perkins) -- Jambalaya (On The Bayou) (Carl Perkins) -- Restless (Carl Perkins) -- Carl Perkins talks about Johnny Cash -- Blue Suede Shoes (Carl Perkins) -- [Unidentified] introduces June Carter Cash -- June Carter talks to the audience -- June Carter recites some lyrics -- The Last Thing On My Mind (June Carter) -- June talks about the Carter Family and introduces the next tune -- I Never Will Marry (June Carter) -- Wildwood Flower (June Carter) -- Worried Man Blues (June Carter) -- June talks about Johnny Cash's new show -- Big River (Johnny Cash) -- Wreck Of The Old '97 (Johnny Cash) -- Johnny Cash talks to the audience and introduces the next tune -- Five Feet High And Rising (Johnny Cash) -- Tennessee Flat Top Box (Johnny Cash) -- Johnny Cash introduces the next tune -- Remember The Alamo (Johnny Cash) -- I Still Miss Someone (Johnny Cash) -- Cocaine Blues (Johnny Cash) -- Johnny Cash introduces the band -- Folsom Prison Blues (Johnny Cash) -- Orange Blossom Special (Johnny Cash) -- I Walk The Line (Johnny Cash) -- Jackson (Johnny Cash, June Carter) -- Johnny Cash introduces the next tune -- Long Legged Guitar Pickin' Man (Johnny Cash, June Carter) -- Ring Of Fire (Johnny Cash) -- Guess Things Happen That Way (Johnny Cash) -- Daddy Sang Bass (Johnny Cash, June Carter, Carl Perkins) -- Folsom Prison Blues (June Carter, Johnny Cash) -- Closing statements
